{{hatnote|Most of the terms used in Wikipedia glossaries are already defined and explained within Wikipedia itself. However, lists like the following indicate where new articles need to be written and are also useful for looking up and comparing large numbers of terms together.}}

{{expand list|date=June 2018}}

This '''glossary of botanical terms''' is a list of terms relevant to [[botany]] and [[plant]]s in general. Terms of [[plant morphology]] are included here as well as at the related [[Glossary of plant morphology]] and [[Glossary of leaf morphology]]. See also [[List of Latin and Greek words commonly used in systematic names]]. You can help by adding illustrations that assist an understanding of the terms.

{{AlphanumericTOC|align=center| nobreak=|numbers=|externallinks=|references=|top=}}

{{Science}}

==A==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= ab- |content= [[wikt:ab-|ab-]] }}
{{defn|defn= A prefix meaning "from, away from, or outside".}}

{{term|term= abaxial |content= [[abaxial]] }}
{{defn|defn= The surface of an organ facing away from the organ's axis, e.g. the lower surface of a lateral organ such as a leaf or petal.}}

{{term|term= abort |content= [[wikt:abort|abort]] }}
{{defn|defn= To abandon development of a structure or organ.}}

{{term|term= abscission |content= [[abscission]] }}
{{defn|defn= The shedding of an organ that is mature or aged, e.g. a ripe fruit or an old leaf.}}

{{term|term= abscission zone | [[abscission|abscission zone]] }}
{{defn|defn= A specialised layer of tissue that allows an organ to be shed by [[#abscission|abscission]] when it is ripe or senescent. Commonly formed, for example, at the base of a [[#petiole|petiole]] or [[#pedicel|pedicel]].}}

[[File:Welwitschia at Ugab River basin.jpg|thumb|right|Members of the genus ''[[Welwitschia]]'' are said to be '''[[#acaulescent|acaulescent]]''']]
{{Anchor|acaulescent}}{{term|term= acaulescent |content= [[wikt:acaulescent|acaulescent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having no apparent [[#stem|stem]], or at least none visible above the ground surface. Examples include some species of ''[[Agave]]'', ''[[Oxalis]]'' and ''[[Attalea (plant)|Attalea]]''.<ref>Shreve, Forrest; Wiggins, Ira. Vegetation and Flora of the Sonoran Desert. Stanford University Press, 1964. {{ISBN|978-0804701631}}</ref>}}

{{term|term= accrescent |content= [[wikt:accrescent|accrescent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Increasing in size with age, such as a [[#calyx|calyx]] that continues to grow after the [[#corolla|corolla]] has fallen, for example in ''[[Physalis peruviana]]''.}}

{{term|term= -aceae |content= -aceae }}
{{defn|defn= A suffix added to the stem of a [[#generic name|generic name]] to form the name of a taxonomic [[#family|family]]; for example, [[Rosaceae]] is the rose family.}}

{{term|term= achene |content= [[achene]] }}
{{defn|defn= A dry, 1-seeded [[#indehiscent|indehiscent]] fruit, e.g. in the genus ''[[Ranunculus]]''.}}

{{term|term= acicular |content= [[acicular (botany)|acicular]] }}
{{defn|defn= Slender or needle-shaped.}}

{{term|term= acropetal |content= acropetal }}
{{defn|defn= Moving from roots to leaves, e.g. of molecular signals in plants.}}

{{term|term= acrophyll |content= acrophyll }}
{{defn|defn= The regular leaves of a mature plant, produced above the base; usually used in contrast to [[#bathyphyll|bathyphyll]].}}

{{term|term= acrostichoid |content= acrostichoid }}
{{defn|defn= (describing a type of [[#sorus|sorus]]) Covering the entire [[#abaxial|abaxial]] surface of a [[#frond|frond]], usually densely so, as in ''[[Elaphoglossum]]'' and ''[[Acrostichum]]''.}}

[[File:Actinoptychus senarius 1260A 14R 1W.JPG|thumb|right|The [[diatom]] ''Actinoptychus senarius'' is '''[[#actinomorphic|actinomorphic]]''']]
{{term|term= actino- |content= [[wikt:actino-|actino-]] }}
{{defn|defn= A prefix that indicates a [[wikt:radial|radial]] pattern, form, or morphology.}}

{{term|term= actinodromous |content= actinodromous }}
{{defn|defn= ([[Parallel venation|leaf venation]]) [[#palmate|Palmate]] or [[Radial symmetry|radially]] arranged venation with three or more [[#primary vein|primary veins]] arising at or near the base of the leaf and either reaching the [[#margin|margin]] or not.}}

{{term|term= actinomorphic |content= [[actinomorphic]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#regular|Regular]]; radially symmetrical; may be bisected into similar halves in at least two planes. Applies e.g. to [[#stele|steles]] and flowers in which the [[#perianth|perianth]] segments within each whorl are alike in size and shape. Compare [[#regular|regular]]; contrast with [[#asymmetrical|asymmetrical]], [[#irregular|irregular]], and [[#zygomorphic|zygomorphic]]. }}

{{term|term= aculeate |content= [[aculeate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Armed with prickles, e.g. the stem of a rose.}}

{{term|term= acuminate |content= [[acuminate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Tapering gradually to a point.}}

{{term|term= acute |content= [[Types of angles|acute]] }}
{{defn|defn= Sharply pointed; converging edges making an angle of less than 90°. Compare [[#obtuse|obtuse]].}}

{{term|term= ad- |content= [[wikt:ad-|ad-]] }}
{{defn|defn= A prefix meaning "near or towards"; also meaning "added to".}}

{{term|term= adaxial |content= [[adaxial]] }}
{{defn|defn= The surface of an organ facing towards the organ's axis, e.g. the upper surface of a lateral organ such as a leaf or petal.}}

{{term|term= adnate |content= [[adnation|adnate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Grown or fused to an organ of a different kind, especially along a [[#margin|margin]], e.g. a stamen fused to a petal. Compare [[#connate|connate]].}}

{{term|term= adventitious |content= [[adventitious]] }}
{{defn|defn= A structure produced in an abnormal position, e.g. an [[#adventitious|adventitious]] bud produced from a [[#stem|stem]] rather than from the [[#axil|axil]] of a leaf.}}

{{term|term= adventive |content= [[adventive]] }}
{{defn|defn= Introduced accidentally (usually referring to a [[#weed|weed]]).}}

{{term|term= aerial |content= [[:wikt:aerial|aerial]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of the air; growing or borne above the surface of the ground.}}

{{term|term= aestivation |content= [[aestivation]] }}
{{defn|defn= The arrangement of sepals and petals or their lobes in an unexpanded flower bud. Compare [[#vernation|vernation]], the arrangement of leaves in a bud.}}

{{term|term= aff., (affinis) |content= [[Species affinis|aff. (affinis)]] }}
{{defn|defn= With affinity to others, akin to; often used for a provisionally recognized but unnamed taxon considered close to that name, perhaps a hybrid or extreme variant.}}

{{term|term= aggregate fruit |content= [[aggregate fruit]] }}
{{defn|defn= A cluster of fruits formed from the free [[#carpel|carpels]] of one flower, e.g. a [[blackberry]]. Compare [[#multiple fruit|multiple fruit]].}}

{{term|term= agricultural weed |content= [[agricultural weed]] }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#weed|weed]].}}

{{term|term= alate |content= [[alate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a [[#wing|wing]] or wings.}}

{{term|term= albumen |content= [[albumen]] }}
{{defn|defn= An older name for the [[#endosperm|endosperm]] of flowering plants. Except for being a [[Storage organ|storage tissue]] for nutrients, it is not at all like the albumen ([[egg white]]) of animal embryos.}}

{{term|term= albuminous |content= [[albuminous]] }}
{{defn|defn= (seeds) Containing [[#endosperm|endosperm]].}}

{{term|term= -ales |content= -ales }}
{{defn|defn= A suffix added to the stem of a [[#generic name|generic name]] or descriptive name to form the name of a taxonomic [[#order|order]].}}

{{term|term= alien |content= [[Alien (biology)|alien]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant introduced to an area outside its natural range. Often synonymous to or used in combination with ''foreign'', ''[[#exotic|exotic]]'', ''non-[[#native|native]]'', and ''non-[[#indigenous|indigenous]]''.}}

{{term|term= alkaloid |content= [[alkaloid]] }}
{{defn|defn= A molecule with a [[nitrogenous base]], often used as a drug, e.g. [[morphine]], [[quinine]], and [[strychnine]], each of which occurs naturally in certain plants.}}

{{term|term= alternate |content= alternate }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= (adj.) Leaves or flowers borne singly at different levels along a stem, including spiralled parts.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= (prep.) When something occurs between something else, e.g. stamens alternating with petals. Compare [[#opposite|opposite]].}}

{{term|term= ament |content= {{linktext|ament}} }}
{{defn|defn= A synonym of [[#catkin|catkin]]. }}

{{term|term= amphitropous |content= [[amphitropous]] }}
{{defn|defn= When the [[#ovule|ovule]] is bent so that both ends are near each other. Compare [[#anatropous|anatropous]], [[#campylotropous|campylotropous]], and [[#orthotropous|orthotropous]].}}

{{term|term= amplexicaul |content= [[amplexicaul]] }}
{{defn|defn= With the base dilated and clasping the stem, usually of leaves.}}

{{term|term= anastomose |content= [[anastomose]] }}
{{defn|defn= Branching and then rejoining, as with [[#leaf venation|leaf venation]].}}

{{term|term= anastomosis |content= [[anastomosis]] }}
{{defn|defn= A connection or fusion of two or more [[#vein|veins]] that are normally diverging or branching, thereby forming a network.}}

{{term|term= anatropous |content= {{vanchor|[[:wikt:anatropous|anatropous]]}} }}
{{defn|defn= When an [[#ovule|ovule]] is inverted so that the [[#micropyle|micropyle]] faces the [[#placenta|placenta]] (this is the most common ovule orientation in flowering plants). Compare [[#amphitropous|amphitropous]], [[#campylotropous|campylotropous]], [[#orthotropous|orthotropous]].}}

{{term|term= androdioecious |content= [[androdioecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of plants, having [[#bisexual|bisexual]] flowers and male flowers on separate individuals. Compare [[#andromonoecious|andromonoecious]], [[#polygamodioecious|polygamodioecious]], [[#polygamomonoecious|polygamomonoecious]], [[#polygamous|polygamous]].}}

{{term|term= androecium |content= [[androecium]] }}
{{defn|defn= Male parts of flower; the [[stamens]] of a flower collectively. Compare [[#gynoecium|gynoecium]]. Abbreviation: A. For instance A 3+3 indicates 6 stamens in two [[Whorl (botany)|whorls]].}}

{{term|term= androgynophore |content= [[androgynophore]] }}
{{defn|defn= A stalk bearing both the [[#androecium|androecium]] and [[#gynoecium|gynoecium]] of a flower above the level of [[#insertion|insertion]] of the [[#perianth|perianth]].}}

{{term|term= androgynous |content= [[androgynous]] }}
{{defn|defn= With male and female flowers in the same [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]].}}

{{term|term= androphore |content= androphore }}
{{defn|defn=  The stalk or column supporting the stamens in certain flowers. }}

{{term|term= andromonoecious |content= [[andromonoecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having [[#bisexual|bisexual]] flowers and male flowers on the same individual plant. Compare [[#gynomonoecious|gynomonoecious]], [[#polygamodioecious|polygamodioecious]], [[#polygamomonoecious|polygamomonoecious]], and [[#polygamous|polygamous]].}}

{{term|term= anemophily |content= [[anemophily]] }}
{{defn|defn= Pollination by wind.}}

{{term|term= angiosperm |content= [[angiosperm]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[flowering plant]]; a plant with developing seeds enclosed in an [[#ovary|ovary]].}}

{{term|term= anisomery |content= [[anisomery]] }}
{{defn|defn= The condition of having a floral [[Whorl (botany)|whorl]] with a different (usually smaller) number of parts from the other floral whorls.}}

{{term|term= anisotomic |content= [[anisotomic]] }}
{{defn|defn= branching with branches having unequal diameters, such as a trunk and its branch, compare to [[#isotomic|isotomic]].}}

{{term|term= annual |content= [[annual plant|annual]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant that completes its life cycle (germinates, reproduces and dies) within one year.}}

{{term|term= annulus |content= [[Annulus (botany)|annulus]] }}
{{defn|defn= Ringlike; in the form of a ring. Pappus bristles are sometimes attached to a ring (annulus or disk) at the top of the achene beak. In some [[pollen]] grains, the exine around the apertures is either thicker or thinner. In pores this border is termed annulus. Having a ring-like constriction (annulus) at the mouth of the flower as in ''[[Huernia]]'' or ''[[Aristolochia]]''. A ring of specialized cells on the [[sporangium]].}}

{{term|term= anthemoid |content= anthemoid }}
{{defn|defn= In [[Compositae]], style with a brush-like tuft of sweeping hairs at the tip of each style branch.}}

{{term|term= anthocarp |content= anthocarp }}
