{{glossary}}

{{term|term= baculiform  }}
{{defn|defn= Rod-like; longer than wide. Compare [[#cylindrical|cylindrical]].}}

{{term|term= barb }}
{{defn|defn= A rear-facing point, as in a [[fish hook]].}}

{{term|term= barbed }}
{{defn|defn= Having [[#barb|barbs]] pointing in one direction.}}

{{term|term= barbellate }}
{{defn|defn= Having barbed hairs (barbellae).}}

{{term|term= bark |content= [[Bark (botany)|bark]] }}
{{defn|defn= The protective external layer of tissue on the stems and roots of woody trees and shrubs; includes all of the living and non-living tissue external to the [[#cambium|cambium]].}}

{{term|term= basal }}
{{defn|defn= Situated or attached at the base.}}

{{term|term= basifixed |content= [[basifixed]] }}
{{defn|defn= Something attached by its base, e.g. an anther attached to the filament. Compare [[#dorsifixed|dorsifixed]].}}

{{term|term= basipetal |content= [[basipetal]] }}
{{defn|defn= developing sequentially from the apex towards the base (i.e. with the youngest towards the base), e.g. of flowers in an inflorescence.  Also, moving from leaves to roots, e.g. of molecular signals in plants.}}

{{term|term= bathyphyll |content= bathyphyll }}
{{defn|defn= A specialized leaf produced at the base of a plant, usually when the plant is immature, and which serves to anchor the plant to a substrate; especially notable in the fern ''[[Teratophyllum]]''. Compare [[#acrophyll|acrophyll]].}}

{{term|term= beak }}
{{defn|defn= A prominent pointed terminal projection, especially of a [[#carpel|carpel]] or fruit.}}

{{term|term= berry |content= [[berry (botany)|berry]] }}
{{defn|defn= An indehiscent fruit with the seeds immersed in the pulp, e.g. a [[tomato]].}}

{{term|term= bi- |content= [[:wikt:bi-|bi-]] }}
{{defn|defn= A prefix meaning "two"; for example, [[#sulcate|bisulcate]], having two sulci or grooves.}}

{{term|term= biennial |content= [[Biennial plant|biennial]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant which completes its life cycle (germinates, reproduces and dies) within two years; usually also forms a basal rosette of leaves the first year and flowers and fruits the second year.}}

{{term|term= bifid }}
{{defn|defn= Forked; cut in two for about half its length. Compare [[#trifid|trifid]].}}

{{term|term= bifoliate }}
{{defn|defn= Having two leaflets (a type of [[compound leaf]]).}}

{{term|term= bifusiform |content= [[bifusiform]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#fusiform|Fusiform]] with a pinch in the middle.}}

{{term|term= bilabiate |content= [[bilabiate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having two lips, e.g. the form of the petals in many [[#irregular|irregular]] flowers.}}

{{term|term= bilateral |content= [[bilateral symmetry|bilateral]] }}
{{defn|defn= Arranged on opposite sides, e.g. leaves on a stem.}}

{{term|term= biloculate }}
{{defn|defn= Having two [[#loculus|loculi]], e.g. in the [[#anther|anthers]].}}

{{term|term= binomial |content= [[Binomial nomenclature|binomial]] }}
{{defn|defn= Making use of names consisting of two words to form the scientific name (or combination) in a Latin form. For example, where the first is the name of the [[#genus|genus]] to which the [[#species|species]] belongs, and the second is the epithet given to that species to distinguish it from others in the same genus.}}

{{term|term= binomial nomenclature |content= [[binomial nomenclature]] }}
{{defn|defn= The system of nomenclature in which the scientific name of a species (and not of a taxon at any other rank) is a combination of two names, the first name being the generic name. The second name is referred to botanically as the [[#specific epithet|specific epithet]]. Note that the two names constitute the species name, not just the second word.}}

{{term|term= bipinnate |content= [[bipinnate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Doubly [[#pinnate|pinnate]]; for example, of a [[#compound|compound]] leaf with individual [[#leaflets|leaflets]] pinnately divided.}}

{{term|term= bipinnatisect |content= [[bipinnatisect]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#pinnatisect|pinnatisect]] leaf with deeply dissected segments.}}

{{term|term= bisexual }}
{{defn|defn= Bearing both male and female reproductive organs; usually, flowers with both stamens and carpels; synonymous with [[#hermaphrodite|hermaphrodite]], [[#synoecious|synoecious]], and [[#monoclinous|monoclinous]]. Bisexual flowers only occur on [[#monoecious|monoecious]] plants. See also [[#androgynous|androgynous]], [[#monoicous|monoicous]], and [[plant reproductive morphology]].}}

{{term|term= bitegmic |content= [[bitegmic]] }}
