{{glossary}}

{{term|term= -eae |content= {{linktext|-eae}} }}
{{defn|defn= A suffix added to the stem of a [[#generic name|generic name]] to form the name of a [[#tribe|tribe]], e.g. ''[[Aster (genus)|Aster]]'' → [[Astereae]].}}

{{term|term= ebracteate |content= ebracteate }}
{{defn|defn= Lacking [[#bract|bracts]]. Synonymous with ''ebracteolate''.}}

{{term|term= ecological amplitude |content= [[ecological amplitude]] }}
{{defn|defn= The range of environmental conditions in which an organism can survive.}}

{{term|term= edaphic |content= [[edaphic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Influenced by or of the soil.}}

{{term|term= elaiosome |content= [[elaiosome]] }}
{{defn|defn= An oily body attached to the seed.}}

{{term|term= elephophily |content= elephophily }}
{{defn|defn= A form of pollination whereby pollen or spores are distributed by the feet of elephants, as in ''[[Rafflesia arnoldii#Reproduction|Rafflesia arnoldii]]''.}}

{{term|term= ellipsoid |content= [[ellipsoid]] }}
{{defn|defn= A three-dimensional shape, [[#elliptical|elliptical]] in all sections through the long axis.}}

{{term|term= elliptical |content= [[elliptical]] (elliptic) }}
{{defn|defn= Planar, shaped like a flattened circle, symmetrical about both the long and the short axis, tapering equally both to the tip and the base; [[#oval|oval]].}}

{{term|term= emarginate |content= [[emarginate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Notched at the apex (notch usually broad and shallow).}}

{{term|term= embryo |content= [[embryo]] }}
{{defn|defn= The young plant contained by a [[#seed|seed]] prior to [[#germination|germination]].}}

{{term|term= emergent |content= emergent }}
{{defn|defn= A plant taller than the surrounding vegetation or, for a water-based plant, one whose leaves and flowers are above the water.}}

{{term|term= enantiostyly |content= [[enantiostyly]] }}
{{defn|defn= The condition in which the [[#gynoecium|gynoecium]] protrudes laterally, to the right ([[#dextrostyly|dextrostyly]]) or to the left ([[#sinistrostyly|sinistrostyly]]) of the [[#androecium|androecium]]. example: ''[[Senna (plant)|Senna]]''.}}

{{term|term= endemic |content= [[endemism|endemic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a natural distribution restricted to a particular geographic region. Compare [[#native|native]].}}

{{term|term= endocarp |content= [[endocarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= The innermost layer of the wall of a fruit; in a [[#drupe|drupe]], the stony layer surrounding the seed.}}

{{term|term= endodermis |content= [[endodermis]] }}
{{defn|defn= The innermost layer of the cortex of [[vascular plant]] roots, also present in the stems of [[pteridophyte]]s. The radial walls are impregnated with [[suberin]] to form a permeability barrier known as the [[Casparian strip]]. }}

{{term|term= endophloeodal|content= [[endophloeodal]] }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#endophloic|endophloic]].}}

{{term|term= endophloic|content= [[endophloic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of [[crustose lichen|crustose]] [[lichen]]s, having the [[#thallus|thallus]] growing within rather than on the bark of trees.<ref name=VMBMLF>''Mosses Lichens & Ferns of Northwest North America'', Dale H. Vitt, Janet E. marsh, Robin B. Bovey, Lone Pine Publishing Company, {{ISBN|0-295-96666-1}}</ref>{{rp|159}} Compare [[#epiphloidal|epiphloedal]] or [[#corticolous|corticolous]] (growing on the surface wood or bark) and [[#endolithic|endolithic]] (growing within rock, not wood).}}

{{term|term= endosperm |content= [[endosperm]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= ([[angiosperms]]) A [[Storage organ|nutritive tissue]] surrounding the embryo of the seed, usually [[triploid]], originating from the fusion of both [[polar nuclei]] with one [[gamete]] after the fertilization of the egg.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= ([[gymnosperms]]) The [[prothallium]] within the [[embryo sac]].}}

{{term|term= endospory }}
{{defn|defn= The production of [[#spore|spores]] that germinate into a reduced multicellular [[gametophyte]] contained within the spore wall. Compare [[#exospory|exospory]].}}

{{term|term= ensiform |content= [[ensiform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Shaped like the blade of a sword.}}

{{term|term= entire |content= [[entire leaf|entire]] }}
{{defn|no=1|1= Not divided.}}
{{defn|no=2|1= (of a [[#margin|margin]]) Having a smooth margin, not lobed or toothed (though possibly wavy or scalloped).}}

{{term|term= entomophily |content= [[entomophily]] }}
{{defn|defn= A form of pollination whereby pollen or spores are distributed by [[insect]]s.}}

{{term|term= ephemeral |content= [[ephemeral]] }}
{{defn|defn= Short-lived. See also [[#caducous|caducous]].}}

[[File:Terengganu roselle.jpg|thumb|right|The enlarged calyx and smaller '''epicalyx''' of ''[[Hibiscus sabdariffa]]'']]
{{term|term= epicalyx |content= [[epicalyx]] }}
{{defn|defn= An [[involucral bract|involucre]] resembling an outer [[#calyx|calyx]], e.g. as in ''[[Hibiscus]]''.}}

{{term|term= epicarp |content= [[epicarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= The outer layer of the wall of a fruit, i.e. the "skin".}}

{{term|term= epicormic |content= [[epicormic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Used to refer to buds, shoots or flowers developing from the old wood of trees, especially after injury or fire.}}

{{term|term= epicotyl |content= [[epicotyl]] }}
{{defn|defn= The part of the plant axis or stem between the [[#cotyledon|cotyledonary]] node and the first foliage leaves.}}

{{term|term= epicuticular wax |content= [[epicuticular wax]] }}
{{defn|defn= A layer of crystalline or amorphous [[wax]] deposited on the surface of the [[#cuticle|cuticle]].}}

{{term|term= epidermis |content= [[Epidermis (botany)|epidermis]] }}
{{defn|defn= An organ's outermost layer of cells, usually only one cell thick.}}

{{term|term= epigynous |content= [[epigynous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Borne on the [[#ovary|ovary]]; describes floral parts when attached above the level of the ovary and arising from tissue fused to the ovary wall. Compare [[#hypogynous|hypogynous]] and [[#perigynous|perigynous]].}}

[[File:Xanthoparmelia angustiphylla.jpg|thumb|right|An '''epilithic''' lichen]]
{{term|term= epilithic |content= [[wikt:epilithic|epilithic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Growing on stone. Compare [[#lithophytic|lithophytic]], a plant growing on stone.}}

{{term|term= epinecral |content= [[epinecral]] }}
{{defn|defn= Dead tissue ([[#necral|necral]]) above the surface of the [[#cortex|cortex]] of a [[lichen]].}}

{{term|term= epipetalous |content= [[epipetalous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of stamens that are attached to the [[#petal|petals]].}}

{{term|term= epiphloedal |content= [[epiphloedal]] }}
{{defn|defn= Growing on the surface of [[#bark|bark]]. Compare [[#endophloedal|endophloedal]] (growing inside, not on, the bark) and [[#epilithic|epilithic]] (growing on rock, not bark).}}

{{term|term= epiphyte |content= [[epiphyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant growing on another plant without deriving nourishment from it (in other words, not a [[#parasite|parasitic]] plant). Compare [[#parasite|parasite]]. Often loosely and incorrectly applied to plants that are not terrestrial (they may grown on various inorganic or organic surfaces), and often to orchids, which are rock-dwelling (and therefore strictly [[#lithophytic|lithophytic]]).}}

{{term|term= epiphytic |content= [[epiphytic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Living on the surface of a plant. Compare [[#lithophytic|lithophytic]].}}

{{term|term= epitepalous |content= [[epitepalous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of stamens that are attached to the [[#tepal|tepals]].}}

{{term|term= epithet |content= [[epithet]] }}
{{defn|defn= The adjectival component in a binomial; the final word or combination of words in a name of more than one word (other than a term denoting rank) that denominates an individual taxon.}}

[[File:Epizoochoria NRM.jpg|thumb|right|Seeds or fruit are dispersed by '''epizoochory''' when they stick to the fur of animals.]]
{{term|term= epizoochory }}
{{defn|defn= A type of seed dispersal that occurs when seeds physically adhere to the outside of vertebrate animal bodies.}}

{{term|term= epruinose |content= [[epruinose]] }}
{{defn|defn= Not [[#pruinose|pruinose]].}}

[[File:Boophane disticha in Phipps Conservatory & Botanical Gardens.jpg|thumb|right|The bases of '''equitant''' leaves enclose later leaves on the stem.]]
{{term|term= equitant |content= [[equitant]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a leaf) Folded lengthwise and clasping another leaf.}}

{{term|term= erect }}
{{defn|defn= Upright, more or less perpendicular to the ground or point of attachment. Compare '''patent''' (spreading). Erecto-patent, between erect and patent.}}

{{term|term= ericoid |content= [[ericoid]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having leaves like those of the European heaths (''[[Erica]]''); small and sharply pointed.}}

{{term|term= erose |content= [[erose]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a [[#margin|margin]]) Irregular as though nibbled or worn away.}}

{{term|term= even-pinnate }}
{{defn|defn= Having an even number of [[#leaflets|leaflets]] in a [[#compound|compound]] leaf. Synonymous with [[#paripinnate|paripinnate]].}}

{{term|term= evergreen |content= [[evergreen]] }}
{{defn|defn= Not [[#deciduous|deciduous]]; having leaves all year.}}

{{term|term= ex }}
{{defn|defn= In nomenclature, indicating that the preceding author proposed the name but did not legitimately publish it, and that the succeeding author referred to the first author when legitimately publishing the name. See [[Author citation (botany)]].}}

{{term|term= exocarp |content= [[exocarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= The outer layer of the [[#pericarp|pericarp]], often the skin of fleshy fruits.}}

{{term|term= exospory }}
{{defn|defn= The production of [[#spore|spores]] that germinate into free-living multicellular [[gametophyte]]s. Compare [[#endospory|endospory]].}}

{{term|term= exotesta |content= [[testa (botany)|exotesta]] }}
{{defn|defn= The outer layer of the [[#testa|testa]] (seed coat). It is derived from the outer [[#integument|integument]] of the [[#ovule|ovule]].}}

{{term|term= exotic |content= [[Introduced species|exotic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Not native; introduced from another region or country.}}

{{term|term= exserted |content= [[exserted]] }}
{{defn|defn= Projected beyond, e.g. stamens beyond the [[#corolla tube|corolla tube]].}}

{{term|term= exstipulate |content= [[exstipulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Lacking [[#stipule|stipules]].}}

{{term|term= extrastaminal |content= [[extrastaminal]] }}
{{defn|defn= Outside the stamens or [[#androecium|androecium]], usually referring to the location of a nectary disk.}}

{{term|term= extrorse |content= [[extrorse]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of anther [[#locule|locules]], opening towards the outside of the flower. Compare [[#introrse|introrse]] and [[#latrorse|latrorse]].}}

