==H==
{{glossary}}

{{term|term= habit |content= [[habit (biology)|habit]] }}
{{defn|defn= The general external appearance of a plant, including size, shape, texture and orientation.}}

{{term|term= habitat |content= [[habitat]] }}
{{defn|defn= The place where a plant lives; the environmental conditions of its home.}}

{{term|term= hafter |content= [[hafter]] }}
{{defn|defn= A flat attachment that forms when the thallus of a [[#fruticose|fruticose]] or [[foliose lichen]]s comes in contact with a substrate, different from [[#rhizines|rhizines]] and [[#hapter|hapter]]s. }}

{{term|term= hair |content= [[hair]] }}
{{defn|defn= A single elongated cell or row of cells borne on the surface of an organ.}}

{{term|term= half-inferior |content= [[half-inferior]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of [[#ovary|ovary]], partly below and partly above the level of attachment of the other floral parts. Compare [[#inferior|inferior]], [[#superior|superior]].}}

{{term|term= halonate |content= [[halonate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a transparent coating, or being of a spore's outer layer.}}

{{term|term= halophyte |content= [[halophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant adapted to living in highly saline habitats; a plant that accumulates high concentrations of salt in its tissues.}}

{{term|term= hand-pollination |content= [[hand-pollination]] }}
{{defn|defn= The controlled act of pollination that excludes the possibility of open-pollination.}}

{{term|term= haploid |content= [[haploid]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having one set of chromosomes, e.g. the complement of chromosomes in each of the cells of the [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]], the nucleus of a [[#gamete|gamete]] and the [[#spore|spores]]. This is expressed symbolically as ''n'', where ''n'' = the gametic number of chromosomes. Compare [[#diploid|diploid]], [[#triploid|triploid]], and [[#tetraploid|tetraploid]].}}

{{term|term= hapter |content= [[hapter]] }}
{{defn|defn= An attachment that may form when a [[foliose lichen]] [[thallus]] comes in contact with a substrate.}}

{{term|term= hastate |content= [[Leaf shape|hastate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Triangular in outline, the basal lobes pointing outwards, so that the base appears [[#truncate|truncate]]; may refer only to the base of a leaf with such lobes. Compare [[#sagittate|sagittate]] which refers to basal lobes pointing backwards.}}

{{term|term= haustorium |content= [[haustorium]] }}
{{defn|defn= In parasitic plants, a structure developed for penetrating the host's tissues.}}

{{term|term= head |content= [[head (botany)|head]] }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#capitulum|capitulum]], a [[#pseudanthium|pseudanthium]].}}

{{term|term= heathland |content= [[heathland]] }}
{{defn|defn= Vegetation dominated by small [[#shrub|shrubs]] which usually have [[#ericoid|ericoid]] leaves.}}

{{term|term= helicoid |content= [[helicoid]] }}
{{defn|defn= Coiled; of a [[#cymose|cymose]] inflorescence, when the branching is repeatedly on the same side (the apex is often [[#recurved|recurved]]). Compare [[#scorpioid|scorpioid]].}}

{{term|term= hemi-legume  |content= hemi-legume }}
{{defn|defn= A legume fruit in which the seed or seeds and one valve of the pod are dispersed as a unit. The valve catches the wind and blows away with the seeds, as in ''[[Acaccia tenuifolia]]'', ''[[Peltogyne paniculata]]''.}} 

{{term|term= herb |content= [[herb]] }}
{{defn|defn= Any [[#vascular plant|vascular plant]] that does not develop a [[#woody|woody]] stem at any point during its life cycle, e.g. a [[Viola|violet]].}}

{{term|term= herbaceous |content= [[herbaceous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Not [[#woody|woody]]; usually green and soft in texture.}}

{{term|term= herbarium |content= [[herbarium]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' herbaria}} A collection of preserved, usually pressed and dried, plant material used for identification and comparison; also a building in which such collections are stored.}}

{{term|term= hermaphrodite |content= [[hermaphrodite]] }}
{{defn|defn= A synonym of [[#bisexual|bisexual]].}}

{{term|term= heteroblastic |content= [[heteroblasty (botany)|heteroblastic]]}}
{{defn|defn= Having parts, especially leaves, that are distinctly different between the [[Juvenile (organism)|juvenile]] and adult stages.}}

{{term|term= heteromorphic |content= [[heteromorphic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having two or more distinct morphologies (e.g. of different size and shape).}}

{{term|term= heterospory |content= [[heterospory]] }}
{{defn|defn= The production of [[#spore|spores]] of two different sizes (small and large) by the [[#sporophyte|sporophytes]] of land plants. }}

{{term|term= heterostyly |content= [[heterostyly]] }}
{{defn|defn= The condition of a species having flowers with different style and stamen lengths, but with all the flowers of any one plant being identical. see:[[#distyly|distyly]]}}

{{term|term= hilum |content= [[Hilum (biology)|hilum]] }}
{{defn|defn= The scar on a seed coat where it separates from its stalk ([[#funicle|funicle]]).}}

{{term|term= hip |content= [[Rose hip|hip]] }}
{{defn|defn= The fruit of a rose plant.}}

{{term|term= hippocrepiform |content= [[hippocrepiform]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[Horseshoe]]-shaped.}}

{{term|term= hirsute }}
{{defn|defn= Bearing coarse, rough, longish hairs. See [[#indumentum|indumentum]].}}

{{term|term= hispid |content= [[hispid]] }}
{{defn|defn= Bearing long, erect, rigid hairs or bristles, harsh to touch.}}

{{term|term= hoary }}
{{defn|defn= Covered with a greyish to whitish layer of very short, closely interwoven hairs, giving a frosted appearance.}}

{{term|term= holotype |content= [[holotype]] }}
{{defn|defn= A type chosen by the author of a name. Compare [[#lectotype|lectotype]].}}

{{term|term= homochlamydeous |content= [[homochlamydeous]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#perianth|Perianth]] not divided into [[#calyx|calyx]] and [[#corolla|corolla]]. Compare [[#dichlamydeous|dichlamydeous]].}}

{{term|term= hort. }}
{{defn|defn= 
{{ghat|(never capitalised) Of gardens, an author citation used in two ways:}}
as a name misapplied by gardeners}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= as an invalid name derived from horticultural writings of confused authorship.}}

[[File:AbbotV1Tab02A.jpg|thumb|right|A '''hypocarpium''' forms below the fruits of ''[[Sassafras albidum]]'']]
{{term|term= hyaline |content= [[hyaline]] }}
{{defn|defn= Translucent; usually delicately membranous and colourless.}}

{{term|term= hybrid |content= [[Hybrid (biology)|hybrid]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant produced by the crossing of parents belonging to two different named groups, e.g. genera, species, varieties, subspecies, forma and so on; i.e. the progeny resulting within and between two different plants.  An F1 hybrid is the primary product of such a cross.  An F2 hybrid is a plant arising from a cross between two F1 hybrids (or from the self-pollination of an F1 hybrid).}}

{{term|term= hybrid formula |content= [[hybrid formula]] }}
{{defn|defn= The names of the parents of a hybrid joined by a multiplication sign, e.g. ''Cytisus ardonoi × C. purgans''.}}

{{term|term= hydrophily |content= [[hydrophily]] }}
{{defn|defn= A form of pollination whereby pollen is distributed by the flow of waters.}}

{{term|term= hypanthium |content= [[hypanthium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A tube or cup-like structure in a flower that includes the bases of sepals, petals, and stamens, and may or may not be connected ([[#adnate|adnate]]) to the [[#ovary|ovary]].}}

{{term|term= hyper-resupinate |content= [[hyper-resupinate]]}}
{{defn|defn= In [[botany]], describing leaves or flowers that are in the usual position, but are borne on a [[Petiole (botany)|petiole]] or [[Pedicel (botany)|pedicel]], respectively, that is twisted 360 degrees. The term is used to describe organs, such as orchid flowers, that are usually resupinate. Compare [[#resupinate]].}}

{{term|term= hypocarpium }}
{{defn|defn= An enlarged fleshy structure that forms below the fruit, from the [[#receptacle|receptacle]] or [[#hypanthium|hypanthium]].}}

{{term|term= hypocotyl |content= [[hypocotyl]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of an embryo or seedling, the part of the plant axis below the cotyledon and node, but above the root. It marks the transition from root to stem development.}}

{{term|term= hypocrateriform |content= [[hypocrateriform]] }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#salverform|salverform]].}}

{{term|term= hypogynous |content= [[hypogynous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Borne below the ovary; used to describe floral parts inserted below the ovary's level of insertion. Compare [[#epigynous|epigynous]], [[#perigynous|perigynous]].}}

{{term|term= hypothallus |content= [[hypothallus]] }}
{{defn|defn= The hypothallus is the outgrowth of [[#hyphae|hyphae]] from under the margin of the [[#thallus|thallus]] of a [[#crustose|crustose]] [[lichens]], connecting the island-like [[#areole|areoles]] into a single lichen.}}

{{term|term= hysteranthous |content= {{vanchor|[[:wikt:hysteranthous|hysteranthous]]}} }} 
{{defn|defn= A type of growth in which new leaves appear after flowering. Also spelled ''histeranthous''. Compare [[#proteranthous|proteranthous]] and [[#synanthous|synanthous]].}}

