==I==
{{glossary}}

{{term|term= idioblast |content= [[idioblast]] }}
{{defn|defn= A cell, especially of a leaf, differing markedly from surrounding cells. They often synthesise specialised products such as crystals.}}

{{term|term= illegitimate name |content= [[illegitimate name]] (''nomen illeg.'') }}
{{defn|defn= A name not abiding by the rules of the botanical Codes, e.g. later [[Homonym (biology)|homonyms]], cultivars that have been Latinised after 1 Jan 1959; [[#cultivar|cultivar]] names with more than 10 syllables or 30 letters; cultivar names that use confusing names of other plants, e.g. Camellia 'Rose'.}}

{{term|term= imbricate |content= [[imbricate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Overlapping each other; of [[#perianth|perianth]] parts, edges overlapping in the bud (the convoluted arrangement is a special form of imbrication).}}

{{term|term= imparipinnate |content= [[imparipinnate]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#pinnate|pinnate]] leaf with an odd number of [[#pinna|pinnae]] (terminated by a single leaflet). Compare [[#paripinnate|paripinnate]].}}

{{term|term= in }}
{{defn|defn= In nomenclature, where the preceding author published the name in an article or book, authored or edited by the succeeding author.}}

{{term|term= -inae }}
{{defn|defn= The suffix added to the stem of a [[#generic name|generic name]] to form the name of a [[subtribe]]: for instance, [[Papaveraceae#Corydalinae|Corydalinae]] from ''[[Corydalis]]'' + ''-inae''.}}

{{term|term= inbreeding |content= [[inbreeding]] }}
{{defn|defn= The production of offspring between closely related parents leading to a high degree of similarity; self-fertilization is the most intense form of inbreeding.}}

{{term|term= incertae sedis |content= [[incertae sedis]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of unknown taxonomic affinity; relationships obscure.}}

{{term|term= incised |content= [[incised]] }}
{{defn|defn= Cut deeply and (usually) unevenly (a condition intermediate between toothed and lobed).}}

{{term|term= included |content= [[included]] }}
{{defn|defn= Enclosed, not protruding, e.g. [[#stamen|stamens]] within the [[#corolla|corolla]].}}

{{term|term= incurved |content= [[incurved]] }}
{{defn|defn= Bent or curved inwards; of leaf [[#margin|margins]], when curved towards the [[#adaxial|adaxial]] side.}}

{{term|term= ined.}}
{{defn|defn= An abbreviation of Latin ''inedita'', an unpublished work. Used to indicate that a botanical name appeared only in a manuscript that was not published, so the name is invalid.}}

{{term|term= indefinite }}
{{defn|defn= variable in number; numerous, e.g. more than twice as many stamens as petals or sepals, or when an inflorescence is not terminated by a flower (and continues growing). Compare [[#definite|definite]].}}

{{term|term= indehiscent |content= [[indehiscent]] }}
{{defn|defn= not opening in any definite manner at maturity; usually referring to fruit. Contrast with [[#dehiscent|dehiscent]]. }}

{{term|term= indeterminate |content= [[Indeterminate growth|indeterminate]] }}
{{defn|defn= unlimited, usually in growth.}}

{{term|term= indigenous |content= [[Indigenous (ecology)|indigenous]] }}
{{defn|defn= native to the area, not introduced, and not necessarily confined to the region discussed or present throughout it (hardly distinct from ‘native’ but usually applied to a smaller area). For example, the Cootamundra Wattle is native to Australia but indigenous to the Cootamundra region of southern New South Wales. Compare [[#endemic|endemic]].}}

{{term|term= indumentum |content= [[indumentum]] }}
{{defn|defn= a collective term for a surface covering of any kind of [[trichome]]s, e.g. hairs, scales.}}

[[File:Starr 080117-1868 Syagrus romanzoffiana.jpg|thumb|right|The leaves of ''[[Syagrus (plant)|Syagrus]]'' palms are [[#induplicate|induplicately]] folded, in contrast to many other palm genera with [[#reduplicate|reduplicate]] leaves.]]
{{term|term= induplicate }}
{{defn|defn= folded upwards, or folded with the two [[adaxial]] surfaces together.}}

{{term|term= indusium |content= [[indusium]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= a membrane covering the [[#sporangia|sporangia]] of some ferns.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= a cup enclosing the stigma in [[Goodeniaceae]].}}

{{term|term= inferior }}
{{defn|defn= of an [[#ovary|ovary]], at least partly below the level of attachment of other floral parts. Compare [[#superior|superior]].}}

{{term|term= inflated }}
{{defn|defn= swollen, like a bladder.}}

{{term|term= inflexed }}
{{defn|defn= bent sharply upwards or forwards. Compare [[#deflexed|deflexed]].}}

{{term|term= inflorescence |content= [[inflorescence]] }}
{{defn|defn= several flowers closely grouped together to form an efficient structured unit; the grouping or arrangement of flowers on a plant.}}

{{term|term= infraspecific |content= infraspecific }}
{{defn|defn= denotes taxonomic ranks below species level, for example subspecies.}}

{{term|term= infrageneric |content= [[infrageneric]] }}
{{defn|defn= denoting taxonomic ranks below the genus level, for example, subgenera, sections, and series.}}

{{term|term= infructescence |content= [[infructescence]] }}
{{defn|defn= the grouping or arrangement of fruits on a plant.}}

{{term|term= infundibular |content= {{vanchor|[[:wikt:infundibular]]}} (infundibuliform)}}
{{defn|defn= funnel-shaped, for example in the [[#corolla|corolla]] of a flower.}}

{{term|term= inrolled }}
{{defn|defn= rolled inwards.}}

{{term|term= insectivorous |content= [[insectivorous]] }}
{{defn|defn= catching, and drawing nutriment from, insects.}}

{{term|term= insertion, point of }}
{{defn|defn= the point at which one organ or structure (such as a leaf) is joined to the structure which bears it (such as a stem). }}

[[File:Calotropis gigantea R.Br. - Flickr - lalithamba.jpg|thumb|right|Stamens of ''[[Calotropis gigantea]]'' are '''inserted''' at the base of the corolla.]]
{{term|term= inserted |content= inserted}}
{{defn|defn= growing out from}}

{{term|term= integument |content= [[integument]] }}
{{defn|defn= in general, any covering, but especially the covering of an [[#ovule|ovule]].}}

{{term|term= intercalary }}
{{defn|defn= (e.g. of growth) occurring between the apex and the base of an organ}}

{{term|term= intercalary meristem |content= [[Meristem#Intercalary meristem|intercalary meristem]] }}
{{defn|defn= a [[#meristem|meristem]] located between the apex and the base of an organ}}

{{term|term= interjugary glands |content= [[interjugary glands]] }}
{{defn|defn= in pinnate leaves, glands occurring along the leaf [[#rachis|rachis]] between the [[#pinna|pinnae]] (occurring below the single, and often slightly larger, gland at or just below the insertion of the pinnae). Compare [[#jugary|jugary]].}}

{{term|term= internode }}
{{defn|defn= the portion of a [[#stem|stem]] between two [[#node|nodes]].}}

{{term|term= interpetiolar |content= [[interpetiolar]] }}
{{defn|defn= of [[stipules]], between the petioles of opposite leaves, e.g in [[Rubiaceae]].}}

{{term|term= intramarginal }}
{{defn|defn= inside but close to the margin, for example a [[#vein|vein]] in a leaf.}}

{{term|term= intrastaminal |content= [[intrastaminal]] }}
{{defn|defn= inside the stamens or [[#androecium|androecium]], usually referring to the location of a nectary disk.}}

{{term|term= introrse |content= [[introrse]] }}
{{defn|defn= of [[anther]] [[#locule|locules]], with opening towards the centre of flower (at least in bud). Compare [[Stamen|extrorse]], [[Stamen|latrorse]].}}

{{term|term= invalid }}
{{defn|defn= Use of names not validly published according to the Code, i.e. they are not strictly 'names' in the sense of the [[International Code of Botanical Nomenclature]].}}

[[File:Malacothrixcoulteri.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.55|Two of these three green [[Asteraceae]] '''involucres''' encase unopened flower heads, and the third supports the open colorful head of emerging flowers. The rows of [[phyllaries]] in this [[Malocothrix coulteri|Snake's head]] appear like the keeled scales of a snake, giving the plant its common name.]]
{{term|term= involucre |content= [[involucral bract|involucre]] }}
{{defn|defn= A structure surrounding or supporting, usually a head of flowers. In [[Asteraceae]], it is the group of [[phyllaries]] ([[bracts]]) surrounding the inflorescence before opening, then supporting the cup-like receptacle on which the head of flowers sits. In [[Euphorbiaceae]] it is the cuplike structure that holds the nectar glands, nectar, and head of flowers, and sits above the bract-like [[#cyathophyll|cyathophyll]] structure. Involucres occur in [[Marchantiophyta]], [[Cycad]]s, [[Fungus|fungi]], and many other groups.}}

{{term|term= involute }}
{{defn|defn= Rolled inwards, for example when the margins of a leaf are rolled towards the [[#adaxial|adaxial]] (usually upper) surface. Compare [[#revolute|revolute]].}}

{{term|term= iridescent |content=[[iridescence|iridescent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a reflective coloured sheen produced by [[structural coloration]], as in the speculum of the mirror orchid ''Ophrys speculum''. }}

{{term|term= irregular }}
{{defn|defn= Not able to be divided into two equal halves through any vertical plane. See also [[#asymmetrical|asymmetrical]]. Compare [[#zygomorphic|zygomorphic]], [[#actinomorphic|actinomorphic]], and [[#regular|regular]].}}

{{term|term= isidium|content= [[isidium]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' isidia}} A warty of club-like structure in some lichens that breaks off and forms new lichens without sexual reproduction. Isidia are dispersed by mechanical means, compared to [[soredia]], which are dispersed by wind.}}

{{term|term= isobifacial |content= [[isobifacial]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of flat structures, especially leaves) Having both surfaces similar, usually referring to cell types or to the number and distribution of [[#stoma|stomata]].}}

{{term|term= isomerous |content= [[isomerous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having an equal number of parts in the [[Whorl (botany)|whorls]].}}

{{term|term= isotomic |content= [[isotomic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having branches of equal diameter. Compare [[#anisotomic|anisotomic]].}}

