{{term|term= maculate }}
{{defn|defn= spotted, marked with spots. }}

{{term|term= Malesia |content= [[Malesia]] }}
{{defn|defn= a biogeographic region comprising Malaysia, Indonesia, New Guinea, and the Philippines.}}

{{term|term= mallee |content= [[mallee (habit)|mallee]] }}
{{defn|defn= growth habit in which several woody stems arise separately from a [[#lignotuber|lignotuber]]; a plant with such a growth habit, e.g. many [[Eucalyptus]] species; vegetation characterized by such plants. }}

{{term|term= mangrove |content= [[mangrove]] }}
{{defn|defn= a shrub or small tree growing in salt or brackish water, usually characterized by [[pneumatophore]]s. Tropical coastal vegetation characterized by such species. }}

{{term|term= margin |content= [[Leaf margin|margin]] }}
{{defn|defn= the edge, as in the edge of a leaf blade.}}

{{term|term= marginal }}
{{defn|defn= occurring at or very close to the [[#margin|margin]].}}

{{term|term= marsh |content= [[marsh]] }}
{{defn|defn= a waterlogged area; swamp.}}

{{term|term= mast |content= [[Mast (botany)|mast]] }}
{{defn|defn= edible fruit and nuts produced by woody species of plants, i.e. [[acorn]]s and [[beech]]mast, that wildlife species and some domestic animals consume.}}

{{term|term= mealy }}
{{defn|defn= covered with coarse, floury powder.}}

{{term|term= medulla }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= In a [[lichen]], the typically undifferentiated tissue underneath the cortex of the [[thallus]], or between the upper and lower [[#cortex|cortex]] if both are present. The [[medulla (lichenology)|medulla]] is analogous to the tissues underneath the [[Epidermis (botany)|epidermis]] (skin) of a leaf. The uppermost region commonly contains most of the [[photobiont]]s.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn=[[#pith|pith]]. See also [[medullary ray (botany)|medullary rays]] in wood.}}

{{term|term= megasporangium }}
{{defn|defn= the larger of two kinds of sporangium produced by [[heterospory|heterosporous]] plants, producing large spores that contain the female [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]]s. Compare [[#microsporangium|microsporangium]].}}

{{term|term= megaspore |content= [[megaspore]] }}
{{defn|defn= the larger of two kinds of spores produced by a [[heterospory|heterosporous]] plant, giving rise to the female [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]]. Compare [[#microspore|microspore]].}}

{{term|term= megasporophyll }}
{{defn|defn= in [[heterospory|hetersoporous]] plants, a modified leaf bearing one or more [[#megasporangium|megasporangia]]. Compare [[#microsporophyll|microsporophyll]].}}

{{term|term= megastrobilus |content= [[megastrobilus]] }}
{{defn|defn= the larger of two kinds of cones or [[#strobilus|strobili]] produced by [[gymnosperms]], being female and producing the seeds. Compare [[#microstrobilus|microstrobilus]].}}

{{term|term= membranous |content= [[Biological membrane|membranous]] }}
{{defn|defn= thin, translucent and flexible, seldom green.}}

{{term|term= mericarp |content= [[mericarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= one segment of a fruit (a [[#schizocarp|schizocarp]]) that splits at maturity into units derived from the individual [[#carpel|carpels]], or a carpel, usually 1-seeded, released by the break-up at maturity of a fruit formed from 2 or more joined carpels.}}

{{term|term= meristem |content= [[meristem]] }}
{{defn|defn= an actively dividing tissue.}}

{{term|term= mesic |content= [[mesic habitat|mesic]] }}
{{defn|defn= moist, avoiding both extremes of drought and wet; pertaining to conditions of moderate moisture or water supply; applied to organisms (vegetation) occupying moist habitats.}}

{{term|term= mesocarp |content= [[mesocarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= The fleshy portion of the wall of a [[#succulent|succulent]] fruit inside the skin and outside the stony layer (if any), surrounding the seed(s); [[#sarcocarp|sarcocarp]].}}

{{term|term= mesomorphic |content= mesomorphic }}
{{defn|defn= Soft and with little fibrous tissue, but not [[#succulent|succulent]].}}

{{term|term= mesophyll |content= mesophyll }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= [[Mesophyll tissue]], photosynthetic tissue of a leaf, the central tissues between the upper and lower epidermis.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In ecology, the blade of a [[leaf]] or leaflet that has a surface area 4500–18225 mm<sup>2</sup>; A plant, or vegetation, that has mesophyll (sized) leaves.}}

{{term|term= mesophyllous |content= [[mesophyllous]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of vegetation) Of moist habitats and having mostly large and soft leaves.}}

{{term|term= mesophyte |content= [[mesophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant thriving under intermediate environmental conditions of moderate moisture and temperature, without major seasonal fluctuations.}}

{{term|term= microsporangium }}
{{defn|defn= The smaller of two kinds of [[#sporangium|sporangium]] produced by a [[#heterospory|heterosporous]] plant, producing [[#microspore|microspores]] that contain the male [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]]. Compare [[#megasporangium|megasporangium]].}}

{{term|term= microspore |content= [[microspore]] }}
{{defn|defn= The smaller of two kinds of spores produced by a [[#heterospory|heterosporous]] plant. Compare [[#megaspore|megaspore]].}}

{{term|term= microsporophyll }}
{{defn|defn= In [[#heterospory|heterosporous]] plants, a modified leaf bearing one or more [[#microsporangium|microsporangia]]. Compare [[#megasporophyll|megasporophyll]]. }}

{{term|term= microstrobilus |content= [[microstrobilus]] }}
{{defn|defn= The smaller of two kinds of cones or [[#strobilus|strobili]] produced by [[#gymnosperm|gymnosperms]], being male and producing the pollen. Compare [[#megastrobilus|megastrobilus]].}}

{{term|term= midrib |content= [[midrib]] }}
{{defn|defn= The central and usually most prominent [[#vein|vein]] of a leaf or leaf-like organ. Also called the [[#midvein|midvein]].}}

{{term|term= midvein |content= [[midvein]] }}
{{defn|defn= see [[#midrib|midrib]].}}

{{term|term= monad |content= monad }}
{{defn|defn= A single individual that is free from other individuals, not united with them into a group. The term is usually used for pollen to distinguish single grains from [[#tetrad|tetrads]] or polyads.}}

{{term|term= moniliform |content= [[moniliform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Resembling a string of beads.}}

{{term|term= monocarpic |content= [[monocarpic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Flowering and setting seed only once before dying. See also [[#semelparous|semelparous]].}}

{{term|term= monochasium |content= [[monochasium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#cyme|cymose]] inflorescence with the branches arising singly. Compare [[#dichasium|dichasium]].}}

{{term|term= monocot |content= [[monocot]] }}
{{defn|defn= An abbreviation of [[#monocotyledon|monocotyledon]].}}

{{term|term= monocotyledon |content= [[monocotyledon]] }}
{{defn|defn= A flowering plant whose [[#embryo|embryo]] contains one [[#cotyledon|cotyledon]] (seed-leaf). Compare [[#dicotyledon|dicotyledon]].}}

{{term|term= monoecious |content= [[monoecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of vascular plants, [[#hermaphrodite|hermaphroditic]], with all flowers [[#bisexual|bisexual]]; or with male and female reproductive structures in separate flowers but on the same plant; or of an inflorescence that has unisexual flowers of both sexes. Compare [[#dioecious|dioecious]].}}

{{term|term= monoicous |content= [[monoicous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of bryophyte gametophytes, [[#hermaphrodite|hermaphroditic]], [[#bisexual|bisexual]], when both male and female reproductive structures develop on the same individual. Compare [[#dioicous|dioicous]].}}

{{term|term= monograph |content= [[monograph]] }}
{{defn|defn= of a group of plants, a comprehensive treatise presenting an analysis and synthesis of taxonomic knowledge of that taxon; the fullest account possible (at the time) of a family, tribe or genus.  It is generally worldwide in scope and evaluates all taxonomic treatments of that taxon including studies of its evolutionary relationships with other related taxa, and cytological, genetic, morphological, palaeobotanical and ecological studies.  The term is often incorrectly applied to any systematic work devoted to a single taxon. Compare [[#revision|revision]].}}

{{term|term= monomorphic |content= [[Polymorphism (biology)|monomorphic]] }}
{{defn|defn= of one type, rather than several. See also [[#dimorphic|dimorphic]] (two types) and [[Polymorphism (biology)|polymorphic]] (many types)}}

{{term|term= monophyllous |content= [[:wikt:monophyllous|monophyllous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a single leaf.}}

{{term|term= monopodial }}
{{defn|defn= a mode of stem growth and branching in which the main axis is formed by a single dominant meristem. }}

{{term|term= monostromatic |content= [[monostromatic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Being a single cell thick, as in the [[alga]] ''[[Monostroma]]''.}}

{{term|term= monotypic |content= [[monotypic]] }}
{{defn|defn= containing only one taxon of the next lower rank, e.g. a family with only one genus, or a genus that includes only a single species.}}

{{term|term= morphology |content= [[Polymorphism (biology)|morphology]]}}
{{defn|defn=  the shape or form of an organism or part thereof.}}

{{term|term= mucro |content= [[Leaf|mucro]] }}
{{defn|defn= Diminutive: mucronule. A sharp, short point, generally at the tip of a leaf or the tip of the midrib of a compound leaf.<ref name="BotGloss">Jackson, Benjamin, Daydon; A Glossary of Botanic Terms with their Derivation and Accent; Published by Gerald Duckworth & Co. London, 4th ed 1928</ref>}}

{{term|term= mucronate |content= [[Leaf|mucronate]] }}
{{defn|defn= terminating in a mucro.}}

{{term|term= multiple fruit |content= [[multiple fruit]] }}
{{defn|defn= a cluster of fruits produced from more than one flower and appearing as a single fruit, often on a swollen axis, as in [[Moraceae]]. Compare [[#aggregate fruit|aggregate fruit]].}}

{{term|term= muricate |content= muricate }}
{{defn|defn= covered with short hard protuberances.}}

{{term|term= mutation |content= [[mutation]] }}
{{defn|defn= an abrupt and inexplicable variation from the norm, such as the doubleness in flowers, changes in colour, or habit of growth.}}

{{term|term= mycobiont |content= [[mycobiont]] }}
{{defn|defn= The [[fungal]] component of a [[lichen]] (compare to [[#photobiont|photobiont]].}}

{{term|term= mycelium (plural: mycelia)|content= [[mycelium]] }}
{{defn|defn= The "vegetative" (nonreproductive) part of a [[fungus]], mostly composed of aggregations of [[hyphae]]. It functions in substrate decomposition and absorption of nutrients.}}

{{term|term= mycobiont |content= [[mycobiont]] }}
{{defn|defn= The [[fungal]] component of a [[lichen]] (compare to [[#photobiont|photobiont]].}}

{{term|term= mycorrhiza |content= [[mycorrhiza]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''mycorrhizal'''}} One of several types of [[symbiosis|symbiotic]] association between a fungus and the roots of a plant.}}

{{term|term= mycotroph |content= [[mycotroph]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''mycotrophic'''}} A plant that obtains most or all of its carbon, water and nutrients by associating with a [[fungus]]. }}

