{{term|term= pappus |content= [[Pappus (flower structure)|pappus]] }}
{{defn|defn= in daisy florets, a tuft or ring of hairs or scales borne above the [[#ovary|ovary]] and outside the [[#corolla|corolla]] (representing the reduced [[#calyx|calyx]]); a tuft of hairs on a fruit.}}

{{term|term= paraperigonium }}
{{defn|defn= Also '''paraperigone'''. Anomalous secondary outgrowth of the [[perianth]]al [[meristem]] with [[Ramification (botany)|ramifying]] [[Vascular tissue|vasculature]]. See also ''[[#perigonium|perigonium]]'', ''[[#perianth|perianth]]'' and ''[[#corona|corona]]''}}<ref>[http://www.amjbot.org/content/86/9/1325.full Alan W. Meerow, Michael F. Fay, Charles L Guy, Qin-Bao Li, Faridah Q Zaman, Mark W. Chase. Systematics of Amaryllidaceae based on cladistic analysis of plastid sequence data. Am. J. Bot. September 1999 vol. 86 no. 9 1325-1345]</ref>

{{term|term= parasite |content= [[parasite]] }}
{{defn|defn= An organism living on or in a different organism, from which it derives nourishment. Some plant species are parasitic. Compare [[#saprophyte|saprophyte]] and [[#epiphyte|epiphyte]].}}

{{term|term= parenchyma |content= [[Parenchyma (botany)|parenchyma]] }}
{{defn|defn= A versatile ground tissue composed of living primary cells which performs a wide variety of structural and biochemical functions in plants.}}

{{term|term= parietal }}
{{defn|defn= Attached to the marginal walls of a structure, e.g. ovules attached to placentas on the wall of the ovary. See [[placentation]].}}

{{term|term= paripinnate |content= [[paripinnate]] }}
