{{term|term= perforation plate }}
{{defn|defn= in a [[tracheary element]], part of the cell wall that is perforated; present in vessel members but not in tracheids. Should not be confused with a [[#pit|pit]].}}

{{term|term= perianth |content= [[perianth]] }}
{{defn|defn= the collective terms for the [[Sepal|calyx]] and [[Petal|corolla]] of a flower (generally used when the two are similar). Abbreviation: P. For instance P 3+3 indicates the calyx and corolla each have 3 elements, or 3 [[sepals]] + 3 [[petals]]}}

{{term|term= pericarp |content= [[pericarp]] }}
