{{term|term= photobiont |content= [[photobiont]] }}
{{defn|defn= In a lichen, the component that does the [[photosynthesis]], the green algae ([[Chlorophyta]]) or blue-green algae ([[Cyanobacteria]]). (compare to [[#mycobiont|mycobiont]], the [[fungal]] component.) Also called the '''[[#phycobiont|phycobiont]]'''.}}

{{term|term= photosynthesis |content= [[photosynthesis]] }}
{{defn|defn= The process by which energy from sunlight is used to convert [[carbon dioxide]] and [[water]] into [[simple sugar]]s in cells containing [[#chloroplast|chloroplasts]]. All plants, except certain [[#parasite|parasites]], can perform photosynthesis.}}

{{term|term= phycobiont |content= [[phycobiont]] }}
