{{term|term= plicate |content= [[pleated|plicate]] }}
{{defn|defn= pleated; folded back and forth longitudinally like a fan, such as the leaves of many palm species. The concept often appears in specific names in forms such as ''[[Kumara plicatilis]]'' and ''[[Acacia plicata]]''. Commonly such names are not correctly appropriate, but are applied to [[Phyllotaxis|distichous]] structures rather than plicate.}}

{{term|term= -[[plinerved]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of leaves) a suffix indicating that the main nerves are lateral and arise from a point distinctly above the base of the leaf. Combined with a numerical prefix to form words like 3-plinerved, 5-plinerved, and so on. Such leaves are especially characteristic of the family Melastomataceae.}}

