{{term|term= polyploid |content= [[polyploid]] }}
{{defn|defn= with more than two of the basic sets of [[chromosomes]] in the [[cell nucleus|nucleus]]; any [[sporophyte]] with cells containing three or more complete sets of chromosomes.  Various combinations of words or numbers with '-ploid' indicate the number of [[#haploid|haploid]] sets of chromosomes, e.g. triploid = 3 sets, [[#tetraploid|tetraploid]] = 4 sets, pentaploid = 5 sets, hexaploid = 6 sets, and so on.}}

{{term|term= polystemonous |content= polystemonous }}
