{{term|term= primary vein |content= primary vein }}
{{defn|defn= The single [[#vein|vein]] or array of veins that is conspicuously larger than any others in a leaf. In [[#pinnate|pinnate]] [[#venation|venation]], the single primary vein can generally be found in the middle of the leaf; in [[#palmate|palmate]] venation, several such veins radiate from a point at or near the base of the leaf.}}

{{term|term= propagule |content= [[propagule]] }}
