==S==
{{glossary}}

{{term|term= saccate |content= [[saccate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Pouched or shaped like a sack.}}

{{term|term= sagittate |content= [[sagittate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Shaped like the head of an arrow; narrow and pointed but gradually enlarged at the base into two straight lobes directed downwards; may refer only to the base of a leaf with such lobes. Compare [[#hastate|hastate]].}}

{{term|term= salverform |content= [[salverform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Trumpet-shaped; having a long, slender tube and a flat, abruptly expanded limb.}}

{{term|term= samara |content= [[Samara (fruit)|samara]] }}
{{defn|defn= A dry, [[#indehiscent|indehiscent]] fruit with its wall expanded into a wing, e.g. in the genus ''[[Acer (plant)|Acer]]''.}}

{{term|term= samphire |content= [[samphire]] }}
{{defn|defn= A common name given to various edible coastal plants, such as ''[[Salicornia]]'' spp. ([[Amaranthaceae]]), ''[[Crithmum maritimum]]'' ([[Apiaceae]]) and ''[[golden samphire|Limbarda crithmoides]]'' ([[Asteraceae]]). }}

{{term|term= saprophyte |content= [[saprophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''saprophytic'''}} An organism deriving its nourishment from decaying organic matter and usually lacking [[#chlorophyll|chlorophyll]]. Compare [[#parasite|parasite]] and [[#epiphyte|epiphyte]].}}

{{term|term= sarmentose }}
{{defn|defn= Having long, slender, [[#prostrate|prostrate]] [[#stolon|stolons]] (runners).}}

[[File:Caloplaca marina.JPG|thumb|upright=0.55|This ''[[Caloplaca marina]]'' lichen is '''saxicolous''' because it grows on stone.]]
{{term|term= saxicolous |content= [[saxicolous]] }}
{{defn|defn= growing on stone, like some [[lichens]].}}

{{term|term= scabrid |content= scabrid {{anchor|scabrous}}}}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''scabrous'''.}} Rough to the touch, with short hard protrusions or hairs.}}

{{term|term= scalariform |content= [[scalariform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Ladder-like in structure or appearance.}}

{{term|term= scale }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= A reduced or rudimentary leaf, for example around a dormant bud.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= A flattened epidermal outgrowth, such as those commonly found on the leaves and rhizomes of ferns.}}

{{term|term= scandent |content= [[Vine|scandent]] }}
{{defn|defn= climbing, by whatever means. See also: [[wikt:Scandent|scandent]] in Wiktionary.}}

{{term|term= scape |content= [[scape (botany)|scape]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''[[#scapose|scapose]]'''}} A stem-like flowering stalk of a plant with radical leaves.}}

{{term|term= scapose |content= [[scapose]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having the floral axis more or less [[#erect|erect]] with few or no leaves; consisting of a [[#scape|scape]].}}

{{term|term= scarious |content= [[scarious]] }}
{{defn|defn= dry and [[#membranous|membranous]].}}

{{term|term= schizocarp |content= [[schizocarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= a dry fruit formed from more than one [[#carpel|carpel]] but breaking apart into individual carpels ([[#mericarp|mericarps]]) when ripe.}}

{{term|term= scion |content= [[wikt:scion|scion]] }}
{{defn|defn= The [[#aerial|aerial]] part of a [[#graft|graft]] combination, induced by various means to unite with a compatible understock or [[#rootstock|rootstock]].}}

{{term|term= sclereid |content= [[sclereid]] }}
{{defn|defn= A cell with a thick, often [[#lignified|lignified]], [[#cell wall|cell wall]] that is shorter than a [[#fiber cell|fiber cell]] and dies soon after the thickening of its cell wall.}}

{{term|term= sclerenchyma |content= [[sclerenchyma]] }}
{{defn|defn= A strengthening or supporting tissue composed of [[#sclereid|sclereids]] or of a mixture of sclereids and fibers.}}

{{term|term= sclerophyll |content= [[sclerophyll]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''sclerophyllous'''}} A plant with hard, stiff leaves; leaves stiffened with thick-walled cells.}}

{{term|term= scorpioid |content= [[scorpioid]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a [[#cyme|cymose]] inflorescence) Branching alternately on one side and then the other. Compare [[#helicoid|helicoid]].}}

{{term|term= scrobiculate |content= [[scrobiculate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having very small pits.}}

{{term|term= scrubland |content= [[scrubland]] }}
{{defn|defn= Dense vegetation dominated by [[#shrub|shrubs]].}}

{{term|term= scurf }}
{{defn|defn= Minute, loose, membranous [[#scale|scales]] on the surface of some plant parts, such as leaves.}}

{{term|term= secondary metabolite |content= [[secondary metabolite]] }}
{{defn|defn= Chemicals produced by a plant that do not have a role in so-called primary functions such as growth, development, photosynthesis, reproduction, etc.}}

{{term|term= secondary species |content= [[secondary species]] }}
{{defn|defn= In [[lichen]]s, a "species" taxon of lichen reproducing only by vegetative means, whose components reproduce mainly by sexual means&nbsp;– cf. [[#primary species|primary species]].}}

{{term|term= secretory tissue |content= [[Plant secretory tissue|secretory tissue]] }}
{{defn|defn= The tissues concerned with the secretion of gums, resins, oils and other substances in plants.}}

{{term|term= section |content= [[section (botany)|section]] (sectio) }}
{{defn|defn= The category of supplementary taxa intermediate in rank between subgenus and series. It is a singular noun always written with a capital initial letter, in combination with the generic name.}}

{{term|term= secund }}
{{defn|defn= Having all the parts grouped on one side or turned to one side (applied especially to inflorescences).}}

{{term|term= sedge }}
{{defn|defn= A plant belonging to the family [[Cyperaceae]].}}

{{term|term= seed |content= [[seed]] }}
{{defn|defn= A ripened [[#ovule|ovule]], consisting of a protective coat enclosing an embryo and food reserves; a propagating organ formed in the sexual reproductive cycle of [[gymnosperms]] and [[angiosperms]] (together, the [[Spermatophyte|seed plants]]).}}

{{term|term= segment |content= [[segment (biology)|segment]] }}
{{defn|defn= A part or subdivision of an organ, e.g. a petal is a segment of the corolla. A term sometimes used when the sepals and petals are indistinguishable.}}

{{term|term= self-pollination |content= [[self-pollination]] }}
{{defn|defn= (also ''selfing'') The acceptance by stigmas of pollen from the same flower or from flowers on the same plant, which means they are self-compatible.}}

{{term|term= semaphyll | content= [[semaphyll]]}}
{{defn|defn= A structure such as a [[bract]] or a [[sepal]] (if the remainder of the [[perianth]] is inconspicuous) which has become modified to attract [[pollinators]]. Plural: semaphylls }}

{{term|term= semelparity | content= [[semelparity]]}}
{{defn|defn= When a plant flowers once then dies.}}

{{term|term= semiterete | content= [[semiterete]]}}
{{defn|defn= Rounded on one side but flat on the other. See also [[#terete|terete]].}}

{{term|term=senecioid |content=[[senecioid]]}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#anthemoid|anthemoid]].}}

{{term|term= sensitive |content= sensitive }}
{{defn|defn= A descriptive term for stigmas that, in response to touch, close the two lobes of the stigma together, ending the receptivity of the stigma, at least for the time that the lobes are closed together. ''[[Mimulus]]'' is perhaps the best-known example.}}

{{term|term= sensu |content= [[sensu]] }}
{{defn|defn= In the sense of.}}

{{term|term= sensu auct. |content= sensu auct. }}
{{defn|defn= (of a plant group or name) As cited by a named authority.}}

{{term|term= sensu amplo|content= sensu amplo }}
{{defn|defn= (of a plant group or name) In a generous or ample sense.}}

{{term|term= sensu lato |content= [[wikt:sensu lato|sensu lato]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a plant group) In a broad sense.}}

{{term|term= sensu strictissimo |content= sensu strictissimo }}
{{defn|defn= (of a plant group) In the narrowest sense.}}

{{term|term= sensu stricto |content= [[wikt:sensu stricto|sensu stricto]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a plant group) In a narrow sense.}}

{{term|term= sepal |content= [[sepal]] }}
{{defn|defn= In a flower, one of the segments or divisions of the outer [[#whorl|whorl]] of non-fertile parts surrounding the fertile organs; usually green. Compare [[#petal|petal]].}}

{{term|term= septicidal |content= [[septicidal]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a fruit) [[#dehisce|Dehiscing]] along the partitions between [[#locule|loculi]]. Compare [[#loculicidal|loculicidal]].}}

{{term|term= septum |content= [[septum (disambiguation)|septum]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' septa}} A partition, e.g. the [[#membranous|membranous]] wall separating the two valves of the pod of [[Brassicaceae]].}}

{{term|term= seriate |content= {{vanchor|[[:wikt:seriate|seriate]]}} }}
{{defn|defn= Arranged in rows.}}

{{term|term= sericeous |content= [[sericeous]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#silky|Silky]] with dense [[#appressed|appressed]] hairs.}}

{{term|term= series |content= [[Series (botany)|series]] }}
{{defn|defn= The category of supplementary taxa intermediate in rank between [[#section|section]] and [[#species|species]]. It is often used as a plural adjective, as in "''[[Primula]]'' subgenus ''Primula'' sect. ''Primula'' series ''Acaules''".}}

{{term|term= serrate |content= [[serrate (botany)|serrate]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#toothed|Toothed]] with asymmetrical teeth pointing forward; like the cutting edge of a saw.}}

{{term|term= serrulate |content= [[serrulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Finely [[#serrate|serrate]].}}

{{term|term= sessile |content= [[Sessility (botany)|sessile]] }}
{{defn|defn= Attached without a stalk, e.g. of a leaf without a [[#petiole|petiole]] or a [[#stigma|stigma]], when the [[#style|style]] is absent.}}

{{term|term= seta |content= [[seta]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' setae; ''adj.'' '''setose''', '''setaceous'''}} A bristle or stiff hair (in [[Bryophytes]], the stalk of the [[#sporophyte|sporophyte]]). A terminal seta is an [[#appendage|appendage]] to the tip of an organ, e.g. the primary [[#rachis|rachis]] of a [[#bipinnate|bipinnate]] leaf in ''[[Acacia]]''.}}

{{term|term= sheath |content= [[Leaf sheath|sheath]] }}
{{defn|defn= A tubular or rolled part of an organ, e.g. the lower part of the leaf in most [[grass]]es.}}

{{term|term= shoot |content= [[shoot]] }}
{{defn|defn= The [[#aerial|aerial]] part of a plant; a stem including its dependent parts (leaves, flowers, etc.).}}

{{term|term= shrub |content= [[shrub]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#woody|woody]] [[#perennial|perennial]] plant without a single main [[#trunk|trunk]], branching freely, and smaller than a tree.}}

{{term|term= sigmoid }}
{{defn|defn= Shaped like the letter 'S'.}}

{{term|term= silicula |content= [[silicula]] }}
{{defn|defn= a stout [[#siliqua|siliqua]] (not more than twice as long as wide).}}

{{term|term= siliqua |content= [[Siliqua (botany)|siliqua]] }}
{{defn|defn= a dry, dehiscent fruit (more than twice as long as wide) formed from a [[#superior|superior]] ovary of two [[#carpel|carpels]], with two [[#parietal|parietal]] placentas and divided into two [[#locule|loculi]] by a 'false' septum.}}

{{term|term= silky |content= [[silk]]y }}
{{defn|defn= Densely covered with fine, soft, straight, [[#appressed|appressed]] hairs, with a lustrous sheen and satiny to the touch.}}

{{term|term= silviculture |content= [[silviculture]] }}
{{defn|defn= The science of [[forestry]] and the cultivation of [[woodland]]s for commercial purposes and wildlife conservation.}}

{{term|term= simple }}
{{defn|defn= Undivided or unsegmented, e.g. a leaf not divided into [[#leaflets|leaflets]] (note, however, that a simple leaf may still be [[#entire|entire]], [[#toothed|toothed]] or [[#lobed|lobed]]) or an unbranched hair or inflorescence.}}

{{term|term= sinuate |content= sinuate }}
{{defn|defn= Having deep, wave-like depressions along the [[#margin|margins]], but more or less flat. Compare [[#undulate|undulate]].}}

{{term|term= sinus |content= [[Sinus (botany)|sinus]] }}
{{defn|defn= A notch or depression between two lobes or teeth in the [[#margin|margin]] of an organ.}}

{{term|term= solitary }}
{{defn|defn= Single, of flowers that grow one plant per year, one in each axil, or widely separated on the plant; not grouped in an inflorescence.}}

{{term|term= soralia}}
{{defn|defn= In a lichen, the structure that bears [[soredium]] for non sexual reproduction.}}

{{term|term= [[soredium]] |}}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' soredia}} In a [[lichen]], a small groups of algal cells surrounded by fungal filaments that form in [[#soralia|soralia]], which break off and grow new lichens without sexual reproduction after being dispersed by wind. Compare to an [[#isidium|isidium]], which breaks off and is dispersed by mechanical means. }}

{{term|term= sp. }}
{{defn|defn= An abbreviation of [[#species|species]] (singular), often used when the [[#genus|genus]] is known but the species has not been determined, as in "''[[Brassica]]'' sp." See [[#spp.|spp.]]}}

{{term|term= spp. }}
{{defn|defn= An abbreviation of [[#species|species]] (plural), often used to collectively refer to more than one species of the same [[#genus|genus]], as in "''[[Astragalus]]'' spp." See [[#sp.|sp.]]}}

{{term|term= spadix |content= [[spadix (botany)|spadix]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#spicate|spicate]] (spike-like) [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]] with a stout, often [[#succulent|succulent]] [[#axis|axis]].}}

{{term|term= spathe |content= [[spathe]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''spathaceous'''}} A large [[#bract|bract]] ensheathing an inflorescence. Traditionally any broad flat blade.}}

{{term|term= spathulate |content= [[spathulate]] (spatulate) }}
{{defn|defn= Spoon-shaped; broad at the tip with a narrowed projection extending to the base.}}

{{term|term= species |content= [[species]] }}
{{defn|defn= A group, or populations of individuals, sharing common features and/or ancestry, generally the smallest group that can be readily and consistently recognized; often, a group of individuals capable of interbreeding and producing fertile offspring. The basic unit of classification, the category of taxa of the lowest principal rank in the nomenclatural hierarchy.}}

{{term|term= specific epithet |content= [[specific name (botany)|specific epithet]] }}
{{defn|defn= Follows the name of the genus, and is the second word of a botanical binomial.  The generic name and specific epithet together constitute the name of a species; i.e. the specific epithet is not the species name.}}

{{term|term= spica |content= [[Spica (botany)|spica]] {{anchor|spicate}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''spicate'''}} A [[#spike|spike]].}}

{{term|term= spike |content= [[Spike (botany)|spike]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''[[#spicate|spicate]]'''}} An unbranched, [[#indeterminate|indeterminate]] [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]] in which the flowers are without stalks. Compare [[#raceme|raceme]].}}

{{term|term= spikelet |content= [[spikelet]] }}
{{defn|defn= A subunit of a [[#spike|spike]] inflorescence, especially in [[Poaceae|grasses]], [[Cyperaceae|sedges]] and some other [[monocotyledon]]s, consisting of one to many flowers and associated [[#bract|bracts]] or [[#glume|glumes]].}}

{{term|term= spine |content= [[Spine (botany)|spine]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''spinose'''}} A stiff, sharp structure formed by the modification of a plant organ that contains vascular tissue, e.g. a lateral branch or a [[#stipule|stipule]]; includes thorns.}}

{{term|term= spinescent |content= [[spinescent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Ending in a spine; modified to form a spine.}}

{{term|term= spiral |content= [[spiral]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of arrangement, when plant parts are arranged in a succession of curves like the thread of a screw, or coiled in a cylindrical or conical manner.}}

{{term|term= splash-cup |content= [[splash-cup]] (sporangia) }}
{{defn|defn= A cup-like structure in [[#cryptogram|cryptogams]] functioning in spore dispersal, whereby the energy of raindrops falling into the cup causes the water to splash back out carrying the spore.<ref>THE SPLASH-CUP DISPERSAL MECHANISM IN PLANTS, Harold J. Brodie, Canadian Journal of Botany, 1951, 29(3): 224-234, 10.1139/b51-022, [http://www.nrcresearchpress.com/doi/abs/10.1139/b51-022#.VCyZGizn_IU]</ref>}}

{{term|term= sporangium |content= [[sporangium]] (sporangia) }}
{{defn|defn= A structure in which spores are formed.}}

{{term|term= sporangiophore }}
{{defn|defn= An organ bearing sporangia, e.g. the cones of ''[[Equisetum]]''.}}

{{term|term= spore |content= [[spore]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[haploid]] propagule, produced by [[meiosis]] in diploid cells of a [[#sporophyte|sporophyte]] that can germinate to produce a multicellular [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]]. }}

{{term|term= sporocarp |content= [[sporocarp (fungi)|sporocarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= A fruiting body containing [[#spore|spores]].}}

{{term|term= sporophyll }}
{{defn|defn= In [[pteridophyta|pteridophyte]]s, a modified leaf that bears a [[#sporangium|sporangium]] or sporangia.}}

{{term|term= sporophyte |content= [[sporophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= The [[ploidy#haploid and monoploid|haploid]] multicellular phase in the [[alternation of generations]] of plants and algae that produces the spores. Compare [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]].}}

{{term|term= sport |content= [[Bud sport|sport]] }}
{{defn|defn= A naturally occurring variant of a species, not usually present in a population or group of plants; a plant that has spontaneously mutated so that it differs from its parent plant.}}

{{term|term= spreading |content= [[spreading]] }}
{{defn|defn= Extending horizontally, e.g. in branches. Standing out at right angles to an axis, e.g. in leaves or hairs.}}

{{term|term= spur |content= [[spur (botany)|spur]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= a short shoot.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= a conical or tubular outgrowth from the base of a [[#perianth|perianth]] segment, often containing nectar.}}

{{term|term= squamule }}
{{defn|defn= (plural squamules, squamulae) small scales; In [[lichens]], squamules are overlapping plate-like forms, sometimes overlapping so much as to become leaf-like, but which lack a lower [[Cortex (botany)|cortex]], unlike the leafy forms of [[#foliose|foliose]] lichens&nbsp;– adjective: [[#squamulose|squamulose]]}}

{{term|term= squamulose }}
{{defn|defn= Covered with small scales ([[#squamules|squamules]]). In [[lichens]], being composed of [[#squamules|squamules]].}}

{{term|term= squarrose }}
{{defn|defn= Having tips of leaves, stems, etc. radiating or projecting outwards, e.g. in the moss ''[[Rhytidiadelphus squarrosus]]''.}}

{{term|term= s.t. |content= s.t.}}
{{defn|defn= An abbreviation for "sometimes". Compare [[#usu.|usu.]] and [[#oft.|oft.]]}}

{{term|term= stalk |content= [[Plant stem|stalk]] }}
{{defn|defn= The supporting structure of an organ, usually narrower in diameter than the organ itself.}}

{{term|term= stamen |content= [[stamen]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''staminate'''}} The male organ of a flower, consisting (usually) of a stalk called the [[#filament|filament]] and a pollen-bearing head called the [[#anther|anther]].}}

{{term|term= staminate flower |content= [[staminate flower]] }}
{{defn|defn= A flower with [[#stamen|stamens]] but no [[#pistil|pistil]] }}

{{term|term= staminode |content= [[staminode]] }}
{{defn|defn= A sterile [[#stamen|stamen]], often [[#rudimentary|rudimentary]], sometimes petal-like.}}

{{term|term= standard }}
{{defn|defn= The large posterior petal of pea-flowers.}}

{{term|term= standard specimen }}
{{defn|defn= A representative specimen of a [[#cultivar|cultivar]] or other taxon which demonstrates how the name of that taxon should be used.}}

{{term|term= stele }}
{{defn|defn= The primary vascular system ([[phloem]], [[xylem]] and [[ground tissue]]) of plant stems and roots. }}

{{term|term= stellate }}
{{defn|defn= [[star (shape)|Star]]-shaped.}}

{{term|term= stem |content= [[Plant stem|stem]] }}
{{defn|defn= The plant [[#axis|axis]], either aerial or subterranean, which bears nodes, leaves, branches and flowers.}}

{{term|term= stem-clasping |content= stem-clasping }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#amplexicaul|amplexicaul]].}}

{{term|term= stenospermocarpy |content= [[stenospermocarpy]] }}
{{defn|defn= The development or production of fruit that is seedless or has minute seeds because of the abortion of seed development. Compare [[#parthenocarpy|parthenocarpy]].}}

{{term|term= sterile |content= [[Sterility (physiology)|sterile]] }}
{{defn|defn= Infertile, as with a [[#stamen|stamen]] that does not bear pollen or a flower that does not bear seed.}}

{{term|term= stigma |content= [[stigma (botany)|stigma]] }}
{{defn|defn= The pollen-receptive surface of a [[#carpel|carpel]] or group of fused carpels, usually sticky; usually a point or small head at the summit of the [[#style|style]].}}

{{term|term= stipe |content= [[stipe (botany)|stipe]] }}
{{defn|defn= (in ferns) The [[#stalk|stalk]] of a [[#frond|frond]]; generally a small stalk.}}

{{term|term= stipella |content= [[stipella]]{{anchor|stipella|stipellae}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''stipel'''; ''pl.'' '''stipellae'''}} One of two small secondary [[#stipule|stipules]] at the base of [[#leaflets|leaflets]] in some species.}}

{{term|term= stipitate |content= [[stipitate]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#stalk|stalked]]; borne on a [[#stipe|stipe]]; of an [[#ovary|ovary]], borne on a [[#gynophore|gynophore]].}}

{{term|term= stipulate }}
{{defn|defn= Bearing [[#stipule|stipules]].}}

{{term|term= stipule |content= [[stipule]] }}
{{defn|defn= A small appendage at the bases of leaves in many [[#dicotyledon|dicotyledons]].}}

{{term|term= stock |content= [[stock]] }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#rootstock|rootstock]].}}

{{term|term= stolon |content= [[stolon]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''runner'''.}} A slender, [[#prostrate|prostrate]] or trailing stem, producing roots and sometimes erect shoots at its [[#node|nodes]]. See also [[#rhizome|rhizome]].}}

{{term|term= stoloniferous }}
{{defn|defn= Having [[#stolon|stolons]].}}

{{term|term= stoma |content= [[stoma]] {{anchor|stomata}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' stomata}} A pore or small hole in the surface of a leaf (or other aerial organ) allowing the exchange of gases between tissues and the atmosphere.}}

{{term|term= striate }}
{{defn|defn= Striped with parallel, longitudinal lines or ridges.}}

{{term|term= strigose |content= strigose }}
{{defn|defn= Covered with [[#appressed|appressed]], straight, rigid, bristle-like hairs; the appressed equivalent of [[#hispid|hispid]].}}

{{term|term= strobilus |content= [[strobilus]] {{anchor|strobili}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' strobili}} A cone-like structure consisting of [[#sporophyll|sporophyll]]s (e.g. [[Pinophyta|conifer]]s and [[Lycopodiopsida|club mosses]]) or [[#sporangiophore|sporangiophore]]s (e.g. in [[Equisetopsida]]) borne close together on an [[#axis|axis]].}}

{{term|term= style |content= [[Gynoecium|style]] }}
{{defn|defn= An elongated part of a [[#carpel|carpel]] or a group of fused carpels between the [[#ovary|ovary]] and the [[#stigma|stigma]].}}

{{term|term= stylodium |content= [[stylodium]] }}
{{defn|defn= An elongate [[#stigma|stigma]] that resembles a [[#style|style]]; a false style, e.g. commonly found in the [[Poaceae]] and [[Asteraceae]].}}

{{term|term= stylulus |content= [[stylulus]] }}
{{defn|defn= the elongated apex of a free [[#carpel|carpel]] which functions like the style of a [[#syncarpous|syncarpous]] [[#ovary|ovary]], allowing [[pollen tube]]s from its [[#stigma|stigma]] to enter the [[#locule|locule]] of only that carpel.}}

{{term|term= subcoriaceous }}
{{defn|defn= Slightly leathery or [[#coriaceous|coriaceous]].}}

{{term|term= subgenus |content= [[subgenus]] }}
{{defn|defn= A category of supplementary taxa intermediate between [[#genus|genus]] and [[#section|section]]. The name of a subgenus is a singular noun, always has a capital initial letter and is used in combination with the generic name, e.g. ''[[Primula]]'' subgenus ''Primula''.}}

{{term|term= subglobose| content=[[:wikt:subglobose|subglobose]] }}
{{defn|defn= Inflated, but less than spherical. See also [[#globose|globose]].}}

{{term|term= subshrub |content= [[subshrub]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also called an '''[[#undershrub|undershrub]]'''.}} A small [[#shrub|shrub]] which may have partially [[#herbaceous|herbaceous]] stems, but generally a woody plant less than {{convert|1|m|ft}} high.}}

{{term|term= subspecies |content= [[subspecies]] }}
{{defn|defn= A taxonomic category within a [[#species|species]], usually used for geographically isolated or morphologically distinct populations of the same species. Its taxonomic rank occurs between species and [[#variety|variety]].}}

{{term|term= subtend |content= [[subtend]] }}
{{defn|defn= To stand beneath or close to, as in a [[#bract|bract]] at the base of a flower.}}

{{term|term= subquadrangular |content= subquadrangular }}
{{defn|defn= Not quite square. Compare [[wikt:quadrangular|quadrangular]].}}

{{term|term= subulate |content= [[subulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Narrow and tapering gradually to a fine point.}}

{{term|term= succulent |content= [[succulent]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= Juicy or fleshy.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= A plant with a fleshy habit.}}

{{term|term= sucker |content= [[Basal shoot|sucker]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#shoot|shoot]] of more or less subterranean origin; an [[#erect|erect]] shoot originating from a bud on a root or a [[#rhizome|rhizome]], sometimes at some distance from the stem of the plant.}}

{{term|term= suffrutex |content= [[suffrutex]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' suffrutices}} A [[#subshrub|subshrub]] or undershrub.}}

{{term|term= sulcate |content= [[:wikt:sulcate|sulcate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Furrowed; grooved. May be single (''monosulcate''), two (''bisulcate'') or many (''polysulcate'').}}

{{term|term= superficial }}
{{defn|defn= On the surface.}}

{{term|term= superior }}
{{defn|defn= Of an [[#ovary|ovary]], borne above the level of attachment of the other floral parts, or above the base of a [[#hypanthium|hypanthium]]. Compare [[#inferior|inferior]] and [[#half-inferior|half-inferior]].}}

{{term|term= suspended }}
{{defn|defn= Of an [[#ovule|ovule]], when attached slightly below the summit of the ovary. Compare [[#pendulous|pendulous]].}}

{{term|term= suture |content= [[suture (anatomy)|suture]] }}
{{defn|defn= A junction or seam of union. See [[#fissure|fissure]] and [[#commissure|commissure]].}}

{{term|term= sward }}
{{defn|defn= Extensive, more or less even cover of a surface, e.g. a lawn grass. Compare [[#tussock|tussock]].}}

{{term|term= sympatric |content= [[sympatric]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having more or less similar or overlapping ranges of distribution.}}

{{term|term= sympodial }}
{{defn|defn= A mode of growth in which the main axis is repeatedly terminated and replaced with a lateral branch. Examples occur in the family [[Combretaceae]], including the genera ''[[Terminalia]]'' and ''[[Combretum]]''.}}

{{term|term= syconium |content= [[syconium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A hollow [[infructescence]] containing [[multiple fruit]], such as that of a [[Common fig|fig]].}}

{{term|term= syn- |content= syn- {{anchor|syn|syn-|sym|sym-}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''sym-'''.}} A prefix meaning "with, together".}}

{{term|term= symmetrical |content= [[symmetry (geometry)|symmetrical]] }}
{{defn|defn= Capable of being divided into at least two equal, mirror-image halves (e.g. [[#zygomorphic|zygomorphic]]) or having rotational symmetry (e.g. [[#regular|regular]] or [[#actinomorphic|actinomorphic]]). Compare [[#irregular|irregular]] and [[#asymmetrical|asymmetrical]].}}

{{term|term= sympetalous |content= [[sympetalous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having united ([[#connate|connate]] or fused) [[#petal|petals]]. See also [[#syntepalous|syntepalous]] (having fused [[#tepal|tepals]]).}}

{{term|term= synangium |content= [[synangium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A fused aggregate of [[#sporangia|sporangia]], e.g. in the trilocular sporangia of the whisk fern ''[[Psilotum]]''.}}

{{term|term= synanthous |content= synanthous }}
{{defn|defn= A type of growth in which new leaves and flowers appear and die back at the same time. See also [[#hysteranthous|hysteranthous]] and [[#proteranthous|proteranthous]].}}

{{term|term= synaptospermy |content= [[synaptospermy]] }}
{{defn|defn= The dispersal of [[diaspore (botany)|diaspores]] as units, where each bears more than one seed, for example where each diaspore comprises an entire inflorescence, as in ''[[Brunsvigia]]'' or multi-seeded fruit as in ''[[Tribulus]]'' zeyheri. ''Ephemeral'' synaptospermy is the term for when the diaspores split into units containing fewer or single seeds each, as in most [[tumbleweed]]s. ''True'' synaptospermy is when the diaspore generally remains entire until germination, as commonly happens in species of ''[[Grielum]]''.}}

{{term|term= syncarpous |content= [[syncarpous]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a [[#gynoecium|gynoecium]]) Composed of united [[#carpel|carpels]].}}

{{term|term= synonym |content= [[synonym (taxonomy)|synonym]] }}
{{defn|defn= An outdated or 'alternative' name for the same taxon.}}

{{term|term= synoecious |content= [[synoecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= A synonym of [[#bisexual|bisexual]].}}

{{term|term= syntepalous|content= syntepalous}}
{{defn|defn= Having fused [[#tepal|tepals]]. See also [[#symppetalous|sympetalous]] (having fused [[#petal|petals]]).}}

