{{Unsourced|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Tapti Pushkaravahini | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = | genre = [[Hindu festivals]] | begins = | ends = | frequency = every 12 years | venue = | location = [[Tapti River]] | coordinates = | country = [[India]] | first = | founder_name = | last = | prev = | next = March 29 - April 9, 2019 | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = Holy Bath | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | people = | member = | website = | footnotes = }} [[File:Major Rivers in India.jpg|thumb|right|260px|Course of the River through the [[South Indian]] Peninsula]] [[Pushkaram]] is the Hindu festival about the 12 auspicious rivers in India. One of the 12 rivers is the river Tapti. Usually, one river is worshipped every year, but sometimes that changes, one of these rivers have a celebration and thousands of people dive in to take a bath as worship. The Rashi or the Hindu zodiac sign for this river is Dhanus or Sagittarius.
